# Case Study: UPI / Online Payment Fraud

UPI and online payment fraud is one of the most common cybercrimes 
affecting students and working professionals in India.
In this type of fraud, cybercriminals try to trick users into
sharing sensitive banking or payment-related information.

A common method begins when the victim receives a phone call, SMS,WhatsApp message, or fake
payment request.The fraudster may pretend to be a bankofficial, customer care representative,
online seller, or even a known contact.They often create urgency by saying that the victim’s 
account will be blocked, money will be refunded, or a prize has been won.

The victim is then asked to click a suspicious link, install a screen-sharing app, scan a QR code, 
approve a collect request, or share an OTP or UPI PIN.Once the victim does this, the fraudster 
gains access to the account or completes unauthorized transactions.

College students are often targeted because they frequently use UPI apps
for food, shopping, travel, and peer payments, but may not always be aware of online scams.

The consequences can include financial loss, account compromise, stress, and misuse 
of personal data.In some cases, victims also lose trust in digital payment systems.
This shows why awareness and careful online behavior are essential.
